ResultSet
ResultSet objects provide access to the tables generated as results of executing Statement queries.

Only one ResultSet per Statement can be open at the same time

The table rows are retrieved in sequence

A ResultSet maintains a cursor pointing to its current row

The next() method moves the cursor to the next row

ResultSet Methods
boolean next() - activates the next row (first call activates first row; returns false if no more rows)

void close() - disposes of the ResultSet, allows you to re-use the Statement that created it